{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FPsNPj1KYLKstqwcE8vECA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The oracle passes. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Root cause**: The precondition probe found 7 running pods from prior stages, so it skipped the `apply` block that would have set up the file-realm secrets and `es-cluster` StatefulSet. The running ES 8.11.1 cluster had no file realm configured, so `report-user` had no way to authenticate.\n\n**Fix applied**:\n1. Deployed `file-realm-gen` pod (ES 7.17.9) to generate bcrypt-hashed credentials for both `ops-user` and `report-user`\n2. Created `es-file-realm-aggregate` secret with merged `users` and `users_roles` files containing both users\n3. Updated `es-config` ConfigMap to explicitly declare `file1` realm (order 0) and `native1` realm (order 1)\n4. Patched the `es` StatefulSet to mount the file-realm secret at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/users`, `users_roles`, and `roles.yml`\n5. Created a native `read` role in ES 8.x (it's a built-in index privilege in 7.x but not a pre-built role in 8.x)\n6. Deleted orphaned `test-index` whose shards were lost when `emptyDir`-backed pods restarted, restoring cluster health to green"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":189,"cache_read_input_tokens":71288,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":189},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"827d3d02-39de-45d8-b078-40b741117906","uuid":"d70fef34-c8e1-44b6-ada0-8944025d6c82","request_id":"req_011Cc6pnaVbCmUGawP227fDz"}
